I am a student in information and communication, i choose the second subject because the reason i decided to follow the cursus of the information and communication is without hesitation my biggest hobby, which is Music.
I am fond of music, I listen to it every day, learn things about It and I even do some with friends of mine. Particculary underground french rap which mean underrated artists. So, I follow these studies with the aim of working with music because I want to have fun working later, I don't know preciselly what I want to do but maybe I could make my own music, maybe i could be the community manager of an artist I like. Two others works who can be link with the music that i could like are graphist for some musicals projects ( create alubms cover, the graphic direction of a project...) or doing the communication / organisations of some musicals events ( concerts, festivals... ).
I listen to music every day since I am fourteen and i really started to interest to it professionnaly since 4 or 5 month only but I never appreciated a thing more than doing music actually. My biggest source of inspiration for that adventure is Alex Dupont, he is a french rapper, not very famous, that i listen since the month of may, I think he is a really interesting rapper because he have is own universe and he is mostly like mine, he use a lot of internet reference of my childhood and even now. Moreover, he Is only eighteen, like me, and that Is very inspirative because when listening to him, I'm thinking that it could be me, he started doing rap at 15 so I have a bit of time to catch to be like him, I have to work hard.
He is the major reason why music inspires me so much everyday.
If you have a little bit of time, I reccomand to you to go listen to his newest album: Luther - Garçon, a unique and immersive piece of art.
